      "content": "That's a fair point about the distinction between a true act of God and poor maintenance. To follow up on that, if the supplier argues that even though the surges are somewhat common in this region, this specific one was so extreme it couldn't have been planned for, how would a court typically weigh that \"unforeseeability\" against the \"reasonable control\" aspect? Basically, where is the line between a known risk and an unforeseeable event?",
